<h2> Form Data - enter</h2>
The idea is, pass parameters from this form to the controller.
<br></br>
Controller will take the parameters and render a new view to display those parameters.
<br></br>
Application: We could take the parameters from a page, pass it to a method inside
the controller.
<br></br>
The controller will run a system command that performs the actions we want it to.
<br></br>
<%= form_tag(:action => "show_data") do %>

<p>Command:
<%= text_field_tag("command","Enter Command you wish to run", :size=> 50)  %></p>
<p>RGen Version:
<%= text_field_tag("rgen_version","Enter Required RGen version", :size => 50)  %></p>

<p>DesignSync Vaults:
<%=check_box_tag("vaults[]", "sync://C55-1T-App-vault",  :size => 5) %> C55-1T
<%=check_box_tag("vaults[]", "sync://C90-TFS-App-Vault", :size => 5) %> C90-TFS

<p>Tools:
<%=check_box_tag("tools[]", "Perl", :multiple => "true", :size => 5) %> Perl
<%= check_box_tag("tools[]", "Python", :multiple => "true") %> Python
<%= check_box_tag("tools[]", "Ruby", :multiple => "true") %> Ruby </p>
<p>Platforms:
<%= check_box_tag("platforms[]","Linux") %> Linux
<%= check_box_tag("platforms[]","Mac OSX") %> Mac OSX
<%= check_box_tag("platforms[]","Windows") %> Windows</p>
<%= submit_tag("Save Data") %>
<% end %>


